  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Frame agreement with NGO (SASK)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The cultivation of flowers, mainly for the European market, is expanding rapidly in African countries. It employs hundreds of thousands of people, especially young women, and provides poor countries with much-needed export revenues. The costs are the increasing environmental risks and social problems, which are addressed with more efficient control and certification systems. The project is in its pilot phase, during which studies will be carried out in each project country to provide information on the special conditions of each country and each union. Once the baseline studies are finished, a decision can be made on the most efficient way for the unions to influence the conditions in flower plantations.</narrative>
  </description>
